<Author>Farnham_Flyer
<Content>Not your average Radisson... As a first trip to Mexico City, I didn't know any better...Colleagues were surprised we were booked in here - it has a reputation locally of hiring out rooms by the hour !Also be very careful to use taxis approved by the hotel - although that is a general rule in Mexico City as per warnings given out by the US Embassy.On the upside, the rooms were well appointed with quality fittings and were spacious, if rather dated. Breakfasts were also good.However, I won't be staying here again - it does not deserve 4 star status. 
