<Content>Zero interest in customer satisfaction Typical business class hotel but I went to two banquet events there in the past year. At the first, besides god awful service, I was ripped off by the hotel valet parkers who slipped me a ticket showing me as arriving early in the AM, rather than in the PM and thus charging me 4 times the rate I should have paid. At the next, I ordered a bottle of wine that was down right rancid, awful smell, no legs, discolored, cork floating all over the place. The waiter got the head of banquets who sniffed and tasted it and told me that Beaujolais is a full bodied strong wine and I must not be accustomed to the taste. When I told him that it is actually supposed to be a lighter red wine and fresh, he dismissed me, refused to change the bottle and charged for it and was sure to add the tip to the bill before presenting it to me so that I could not take revenge. This place should be closed down or clausurado as we say here for incompetent staff who rob its clientele, rather than serve them. God knows where the manager is when such things go on. My only two visits to this hotel and I will never return - I would rather dine at McDonald's for higher quality service and food than their four star claim. 
